<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>The Unknown</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Euthinasia">Euthinasia</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:34 p.m. 1/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> The Unknown<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I hope to God that there are more things in the final that are not known or documented then are.

<P>For instance, the broken alters and ruins that scatter the land, I would love for them to have a secret meaning that would take months of research to figure out. Of course we would need more variable to unlock some of this such as phases of the moon or star alignment (a star scape of diffrent magnatudes would be so easy).
<P>Example, when the moon is full and The Bear Constilation is at the zeneth and the bright red star can be seen in the south, if the word "Analnathrac" is said standing in the ruins of the ferrot forest then a mighty deamon is summoned and sent to Freeport to reak havok on the town.
<P>Or durring a rainstorm if a tower shild is held and you sit down and chant Some ancient text you found in a previouse quest AND you worship the rain god, your shild is struk and charged with a bash of lightning bonus.
<P>Really detailed stuff like this that dedicated players could discover would be great for those who persue knowledge.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
